<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
@KJ{{five^grade}} verbs form the @HI{{masu}}-stem by changing the final kana to the @HI{{i}}-row.
To form the @HI{{masu}}-form, append @HI{{masu}} to this stem.
</p>

<p>
@KJ{{ichi^grade}} verbs form the @HI{{masu}}-stem by dropping the final @HI{{ru}}.
To form the @HI{{masu}}-form, append @HI{{masu}} to this stem.
</p>

<p>
The two irregular verbs conjugate as shown above.
</p>

<p>
The @HI{{masu}}-stem is also known as the verb stem, or sometimes as the infinitive.
</p>

